# Design System Rules

**Before creating ANY component, search `src/components/ui` for an existing reusable
solution.** Creating a one-off variant of an existing primitive is a bug.

## Shared Primitives (use these, never re-implement)

- **Typography** — heading/text components and Tailwind text scale; no ad-hoc font
  sizes.
- **Spacing** — Tailwind spacing scale only; no arbitrary pixel values.
- **Cards** — `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardContent` for all panel surfaces.
- **Forms** — `Input`, `Select`, `Textarea`, `Field` (label + error) wired to React
  Hook Form + Zod. Every form uses `useForm` with a `zodResolver` and a shared schema.
- **Tables** — `Table` primitives for all tabular data (availability, tenants,
  contacts, documents).
- **Modals** — the shared `Modal`/`Dialog` system for all overlays; never hand-roll a
  fixed-position overlay.
- **Buttons & Badges** — shared variants (`primary | secondary | ghost | danger`,
  status badges).
- **Map components** — shared map preview/embed components in `src/features/maps`;
  never instantiate the Maps SDK directly in a page.
- **Canvas components** — shared canvas/editor building blocks live in
  `src/features/site-plan-studio`; tools are registry plugins, not bespoke handlers.

## Conventions

- `cn()` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes.
- Variants via explicit prop unions, not boolean prop explosions.
- Components are presentational; data fetching lives in feature hooks (React Query).
